The term "bell curve" originates from the fact that the graph used to depict a normal distribution consists of a symmetrical bell-shaped curve.The highest point on the curve. or the top of the bell. represents the most probable event in a series of data (its mean. mode. and median in this case). while all other possible occurrences are symmetrically distributed around the mean. creating a downward-sloping curve on each side of the peak. The width of the bell curve is described by its standard deviation.
